channel.title: A Few Questions, Servers already running fine
channel.description: Ok you dont have to answer all of them. 1. How do i delete an npc (theres a shop in my server that dc's you every time you trade him) 2. My compiler wont work i downloaded kdj like 6 times but it says i dont have it downloaded. 3. how do i change the words in the chatbox and the words at the top of the screen.

item.title: A Few Questions, Servers already running fine
item.dc:creator: @N11 -N-
item.description:
@N11 wrote:

Right click your compiler and hit “Edit”. Ctrl + F “JDK” and where it says JDK and numbers like JDK1.5.0_05\BIN or the “5” is a different number. Just change it to 6.

item.title: A Few Questions, Servers already running fine
item.dc:creator: @magep00ner12 magep00ner12
item.description:
@magep00ner12 wrote:

  1. Go to your autospawn.cfg file and there you will see a list of spawned npc’s. delete the one you want to.
  2. Try this compiler:

@echo off if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

  1. Go into client.java and search for the words that you see in the chatbox. Then when u found them you can edit them
